The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, April 5: The rupee continued its upward march against the dollar in a volatile trade today. The Indian currency closed at an eight-year high of 42.92 per dollar following a late bout of selling of the greenback by foreign and nationalised banks. On Wednesday, though the rupee hit an intra-day high of 42.84, it ended off these highs because the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) intervened. 

 New Delhi, April 5: After remaining unchanged for three weeks, inflation eased to 6.39 per cent for the week ended March 24 due to lower prices of some food items and manufactured products.

 London, April 5: The Tatas will make the payment for its $12-billion takeover of the Corus group on April 11. This is the last step in completing the largest overseas acquisition by the Indian firm.

 New Delhi, April 5: Decline in the performance of the cement and electricity sectors pulled down the growth index of six core infrastructure industries to 7.2 per cent in February this year from 9.1 per cent in the same month of 2006.

 Mumbai, April 5: Lupin has sold certain patent applications and other related intellectual property for Perindopril (hypertension drug) to French firm Laboratories Servier for Rs 115.31 crore.




